American Railcar Industries, Inc. (NASDAQ:ARII) Receives An Update From Brokers


 By Ashley Brown /  in  Stocks /  on  Friday, 21 Jul 2017 06:00 AM  / 0 Comments




Analysts reviewing American Railcar Industries, Inc. have recently updated their recommended buy/sell ratings and price targets on the stock.  			         



Based on their most recently released notes to investors, 0 analysts have a rating of “buy”, 1 analysts “outperform”, 4 analysts “hold”, 0 analysts “underperform” and 0 analysts “sell”.
Ratings and price target breakdown:
 06/21/2017 – Buckingham Research began new coverage on American Railcar Industries, Inc. giving the company a “” rating. They now have a USD 38 price target on the stock.
 03/20/2017 – American Railcar Industries, Inc. was upgraded to “” by analysts at Cowen. They now have a USD 45 price target on the stock.
 12/19/2016 – American Railcar Industries, Inc. was downgraded to “” by analysts at Standpoint Research.
 02/22/2016 – American Railcar Industries, Inc. was downgraded to “” by analysts at BB&T Capital Markets.
 10/19/2015 – American Railcar Industries, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Stifel Nicolaus. They now have a USD 38 price target on the stock.
 09/28/2015 – American Railcar Industries, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at UBS. They now have a USD 41 price target on the stock.
 09/10/2014 – American Railcar Industries, Inc. was downgraded to “” by analysts at Zacks. They now have a USD 84.8 price target on the stock.
 02/25/2014 – American Railcar Industries, Inc. had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Stephens. They now have a USD 48 price target on the stock.
 02/12/2014 – American Railcar Industries, Inc. was downgraded to “” by analysts at Longbow Research. They now have a USD 45 price target on the stock.
 11/21/2013 – American Railcar Industries, Inc. was downgraded to “” by analysts at Raymond James. They now have a USD 44 price target on the stock.
 10/17/2013 – American Railcar Industries, Inc. was downgraded to “” by analysts at Avondale Partners.
American Railcar Industries, Inc. has a 50 day moving average of 36.66 and a 200 day moving average of 40.93. The stock’s market capitalization is 707.03M, it has a 52-week low of 34.50 and a 52-week high of 51.10. 
The share price of the company (NASDAQ:ARII) was down -1.72%, with a high of 37.82 during the day and the volume of American Railcar Industries, Inc. shares traded was 88465.  



American Railcar Industries, Inc. is a designer and manufacturer of hopper and tank railcars. The Company designs and manufactures railcars and a range of components for the North American railcar and industrial markets. It operates through three segments: manufacturing, railcar leasing and railcar services. The Company’s Manufacturing segment consists of railcar manufacturing and railcar and industrial component manufacturing. The Railcar leasing segment consists of railcars manufactured by it and leased to third parties under operating leases. The Railcar services segment consists of railcar repair, engineering and field services. As of December 31, 2016, the Company’s operations included eight manufacturing plants that fabricate and assemble raw materials, mainly steel, into railcars, railcar components and industrial components; eight railcar repair plants; and 11 mobile repair (mobile units) and mini repair shop (mini shop) locations.


